fields.name: KEY
fields.desc: Stores AES keys.

fields.name: TEXT_IN
fields.desc: Stores the source data when the AES Accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

fields.name: TEXT_OUT
fields.desc: Stores the result data when the AES Accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc:
Defines the operation type of the AES Accelerator operating under the Typical AES working mode.
&
0x0(AES_EN_128): AES-EN-128 #
0x1(AES_EN_192): AES-EN-192 #
0x2(AES_EN_256): AES-EN-256 #
0x4(AES_DE_128): AES-DE-128 #
0x5(AES_DE_192): AES-DE-192 #
0x6(AES_DE_256): AES-DE-256 
&

fields.name: ENDIAN
fields.desc:
Defines the endianness of input and output texts.
&
[1:0] key endian #
[3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian #
[5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian #
&

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to start AES operation.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc:
Stores the working status of the AES Accelerator. For details, see Table 3 for Typical AES working mode and Table 9 for DMA AES working mode.
For typical AES; 0 = idle; 1 = busy.
For DMA-AES; 0 = idle; 1 = busy; 2 = calculation_done.

fields.name: IV
fields.desc: This register stores the %sth 32-bit piece of 128-bit initialization vector

fields.name: H
fields.desc: GCM hash subkey

fields.name: J0
fields.desc: This register stores the %sth 32-bit piece of 128-bit J0

fields.name: T0
fields.desc: This register stores the %sth 32-bit piece of 128-bit T0

fields.name: DMA_ENABLE
fields.desc:
Defines the working mode of the AES Accelerator. For details, see Table 1.
1'h0: typical AES operation
1'h1: DMA-AES operation

fields.name: BLOCK_MODE
fields.desc:
Defines the operation type of the AES Accelerator operating under the DMA-AES working mode. For details, see Table 8.
&
3'h0(BLOCK_MODE_ECB): ECB #
3'h1(BLOCK_MODE_CBC): CBC #
3'h2(BLOCK_MODE_OFB): OFB #
3'h3(BLOCK_MODE_CTR): CTR #
3'h4(BLOCK_MODE_CFB8): CFB-8 #
3'h5(BLOCK_MODE_CFB128): CFB-128 #
3'h6(BLOCK_MODE_GCM): GCM
&

fields.name: BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Stores the Block Number of plaintext or cipertext when the AES Accelerator operates under the DMA-AES working mode. For details, see Section 1.5.4.

fields.name: INC_SEL
fields.desc: Defines the Standard Incrementing Function for CTR block operation. Set this bit to 0 or 1 to choose INC 32 or INC 128 .

fields.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Stores the ADD Block Number for the GCM operation.

fields.name: REMAINDER_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: Stores the Remainder Bit Number for the GCM operation.

fields.name: CONTINUE_OP
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to continue AES operation.

fields.name: INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to clear AES interrupt.

fields.name: INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable AES interrupt and 0 to disable interrupt.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: DMA_EXIT
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to exit AES operation. This register is only effective for DMA-AES operation.

fields.desc: Set this bit to disable Dcache.

fields.name: DIS_DOWNLOAD_ICACHE
fields.desc: Disables Icache when SoC is in Download mode.

fields.name: DIS_DOWNLOAD_DCACHE
fields.desc: Disables Dcache when SoC is in Download mode.

fields.name: DIS_FORCE_DOWNLOAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable the function that forces chip into download mode.

fields.name: DIS_USB
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable USB OTG function.

fields.name: DIS_CAN
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable the TWAI Controller function.

fields.name: DIS_BOOT_REMAP
fields.desc: Disables capability to Remap RAM to ROM address space.

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED5
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: SOFT_DIS_JTAG
fields.desc: Software disables JTAG. When software disabled, JTAG can be activated temporarily by HMAC peripheral.

fields.name: HARD_DIS_JTAG
fields.desc: Hardware disables JTAG permanently.

fields.name: DIS_DOWNLOAD_MANUAL_ENCRYPT
fields.desc: Disables flash encryption when in download boot modes.

fields.name: USB_DREFH
fields.desc: Controls single-end input threshold vrefh, 1.76 V to 2 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

fields.name: USB_DREFL
fields.desc: Controls single-end input threshold vrefl, 0.8 V to 1.04 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

fields.name: USB_EXCHG_PINS
fields.desc: Set this bit to exchange USB D+ and D- pins.

fields.name: EXT_PHY_ENABLE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable external USB PHY.

fields.name: USB_FORCE_NOPERSIST
fields.desc: If set, forces USB BVALID to 1.

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED0
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: VDD_SPI_MODECURLIM
fields.desc: SPI regulator switches current limit mode.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_DREFH
fields.desc: SPI regulator high voltage reference.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_DREFM
fields.desc: SPI regulator medium voltage reference.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_DREFL
fields.desc: SPI regulator low voltage reference.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_XPD
fields.desc: If VDD_SPI_FORCE is 1, this value determines if the VDD_SPI regulator is powered on.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_TIEH
fields.desc: If VDD_SPI_FORCE is 1, determines VDD_SPI voltage. 0: VDD_SPI connects to 1.8 V LDO. 1: VDD_SPI connects to VDD_RTC_IO.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_FORCE
fields.desc: Set this bit to use XPD_VDD_PSI_REG and VDD_SPI_TIEH to configure VDD_SPI LDO.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_EN_INIT
fields.desc: Set SPI regulator to 0 to configure init[1:0]=0.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_ENCURLIM
fields.desc: Set SPI regulator to 1 to enable output current limit.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_DCURLIM
fields.desc: Tunes the current limit threshold of SPI regulator when tieh=0, about 800 mA/(8+d).

fields.name: VDD_SPI_INIT
fields.desc: Adds resistor from LDO output to ground. 0: no resistance. 1: 6 K. 2: 4 K. 3: 2 K.

fields.name: VDD_SPI_DCAP
fields.desc: Prevents SPI regulator from overshoot.

fields.name: WDT_DELAY_SEL
fields.desc: Selects RTC watchdog timeout threshold at startup. 0: 40,000 slow clock cycles. 1: 80,000 slow clock cycles. 2: 160,000 slow clock cycles. 3: 320,000 slow clock cycles.

fields.name: SPI_BOOT_CRYPT_CNT
fields.desc: Enables encryption and decryption, when an SPI boot mode is set. Feature is enabled 1 or 3 bits are set in the eFuse, disabled otherwise.

fields.name: SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE0
fields.desc: If set, revokes use of secure boot key digest 0.

fields.name: SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE1
fields.desc: If set, revokes use of secure boot key digest 1.

fields.name: SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE2
fields.desc: If set, revokes use of secure boot key digest 2.

fields.desc: Set this bit to enable secure boot.

fields.desc: Set this bit to enable aggressive secure boot key revocation mode.

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED1
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: FLASH_TPUW
fields.desc: Configures flash startup delay after SoC power-up, in unit of (ms/2). When the value is 15, delay is 7.5 ms.

fields.name: DIS_DOWNLOAD_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable all download boot modes.

fields.name: DIS_LEGACY_SPI_BOOT
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable Legacy SPI boot mode.

fields.name: UART_PRINT_CHANNEL
fields.desc: Selects the default UART for printing boot messages. 0: UART0. 1: UART1.

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED3
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: DIS_USB_DOWNLOAD_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to disable use of USB OTG in UART download boot mode.

fields.name: ENABLE_SECURITY_DOWNLOAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable secure UART download mode (read/write flash only).

fields.name: UART_PRINT_CONTROL
fields.desc: Set the default UART boot message output mode. 00: Enabled. 01: Enable when GPIO46 is low at reset. 10: Enable when GPIO46 is high at reset. 11: Disabled.

fields.name: PIN_POWER_SELECTION
fields.desc: Set default power supply for GPIO33-GPIO37, set when SPI flash is initialized. 0: VDD3P3_CPU. 1: VDD_SPI.

fields.name: FLASH_TYPE
fields.desc: SPI flash type. 0: maximum four data lines, 1: eight data lines.

fields.name: FORCE_SEND_RESUME
fields.desc: If set, forces ROM code to send an SPI flash resume command during SPI boot.

fields.name: SECURE_VERSION
fields.desc: Secure version (used by ESP-IDF anti-rollback feature).

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED2
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: RPT4_RESERVED4
fields.desc: Reserved (used for four backups method).

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate preload operation is finished.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_UNLOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_UNLOCK_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate unlock operation is finished.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate lock operation is finished.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_MASK_BUS0
fields.desc: The bit is used to disable dbus0, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_MASK_BUS1
fields.desc: The bit is used to disable dbus1, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_MASK_BUS2
fields.desc: The bit is used to disable dbus2, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to close clock gating of dcache tag memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: The bit is used to power dcache tag memory down, 0: follow  rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power down

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power dcache tag memory down, 0: follow  rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power up

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK0_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the first start virtual address of data locking, which is combined with PRO_DCACHE_LOCK0_SIZE_REG

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK0_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the first length of data locking, which is combined with PRO_DCACHE_LOCK0_ADDR_REG

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK1_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the second start virtual address of data locking, which is combined with PRO_DCACHE_LOCK1_SIZE_REG

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_LOCK1_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the second length of data locking, which is combined with PRO_DCACHE_LOCK1_ADDR_REG

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_MEMSYNC_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address for invalidate, flush, clean, lock and unlock operations. The manual operations will be issued if the address is validate. The auto operations will be issued if the address is invalidate. It should be combined with PRO_DCACHE_MEM_SYNC1.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_MEMSYNC_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length for invalidate, flush, clean, lock and unlock operations. The manual operations will be issued if it is validate. The auto operations will be issued if it is invalidate. It should be combined with PRO_DCACHE_MEM_SYNC0.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address for manual pre-load operation. It should be combined with PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE_REG.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length for manual pre-load operation.  It should be combined with PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR_REG..

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_PRELOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the direction of manual pre-load operation. 1: descending, 0: ascending.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_MODE
fields.desc: Reserved.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_STEP
fields.desc: Reserved.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the direction of conditional pre-load operation. 1: descending, 0: ascending.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_RQST
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure trigger conditions for conditional pre-load. 0/3: cache miss, 1: cache hit, 2: both cache miss and hit.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the numbers of the cache block for the issuing conditional pre-load operation.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA
fields.desc: The bits are used to enable the first section for conditional pre-load operation.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR

fields.name: PRO_ICACHE_ENABLE

fields.name: PRO_ICACHE_SETSIZE_MODE

fields.name: PRO_ICACHE_BLOCKSIZE_MODE

fields.desc: Invert the input value. 1: invert enabled; 0: invert disabled.

fields.name: SEL

If a value 256 is written to this field, bit n of GPIO_OUT_REG/GPIO_OUT1_REG and GPIO_ENABLE_REG/GPIO_ENABLE1_REG will be selected as the output value and output enable.

fields.name: INV_SEL

fields.name: OEN_INV_SEL

fields.name: SCL_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc: 0: direct output. 1: open drain output.

fields.name: TRANS_START

fields.name: TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the sending mode for data needing to be sent.

1: send data from the least significant bit.

0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
This bit is used to control the storage mode for received data.

1: receive data from the least significant bit.

0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.desc: This register is used to control the REF_TICK.

fields.desc: The received ACK value in master mode or slave mode. 0: ACK. 1: NACK.

fields.name: SLAVE_RW
fields.desc: When in slave mode, 1: master reads from slave. 0: master writes to slave.

fields.name: TIME_OUT
fields.desc: When the I2C controller takes more than I2C_TIME_OUT clocks to receive a data bit, this field changes to 1.

fields.name: ARB_LOST
fields.desc: When the I2C controller loses control of SCL line, this register changes to 1.

fields.name: BUS_BUSY
fields.desc: 1: the I2C bus is busy transferring data. 0: the I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: SLAVE_ADDRESSED
fields.desc: When configured as an I2C Slave, and the address sent by the master is equal to the address of the slave, then this bit will be of high level.

fields.name: BYTE_TRANS
fields.desc: This field changes to 1 when one byte is transferred.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field represents the amount of data needed to be sent.

fields.name: STRETCH_CAUSE
fields.desc: The cause of stretching SCL low in slave mode. 0:  stretching SCL low at the beginning of I2C read data state. 1: stretching SCL low when I2C TX FIFO is empty in slave mode. 2: stretching SCL low when I2C RX FIFO is full in slave mode.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: This field stores the amount of received data in RAM.

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the I2C module state machine.

0: Idle. 1: Address shift. 2: ACK address. 3: RX data. 4: TX data. 5: Send ACK. 6: Wait ACK

fields.name: SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
This field indicates the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.

0: Idle. 1: Start. 2: Negative edge. 3: Low. 4: Positive edge. 5: High. 6: Stop

fields.desc: This field is used to enable the slave 10-bit addressing mode in master mode.

fields.name: TXFIFO_START_ADDR

This is the offset address of the last sent data, as described in  I2C_NONFIFO_TX_THRES.

The value refreshes when an I2C_TXFIFO_OVF_INT or I2C_TRANS_COMPLETE_INT interrupt is generated.

fields.name: TX_UPDATE

fields.name: TXFIFO_WM_THRHD

fields.name: NONFIFO_TX_THRES
fields.desc: When I2C sends more than I2C_NONFIFO_TX_THRES bytes of data, it will generate an I2C_TXFIFO_OVF_INT interrupt and update the current offset address of the sent data.

1061236784.name: SDA_HOLD
1061236784.desc: Configures the hold time after a negative SCL edge

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the interval between changing the SDA output level and the falling edge of SCL, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236788.name: SDA_SAMPLE
1061236788.desc: Configures the sample time after a positive SCL edge

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the interval between the rising edge of SCL and the level sampling time of SDA, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236792.name: SCL_HIGH_PERIOD
1061236792.desc: Configures the high level width of the SCL clock

fields.name: SCL_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SCL_WAIT_HIGH_PERIOD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure for the SCL_FSM's waiting period for SCL to go high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236800.name: SCL_START_HOLD
1061236800.desc: Configures the interval between pulling SDA low and pulling SCL low when the master generates a START condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure  interval between pulling SDA low and pulling SCL low when the master generates a START condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236804.name: SCL_RSTART_SETUP
1061236804.desc: Configures the interval between the positive edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the interval between the positive edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA for a RESTART condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236808.name: SCL_STOP_HOLD
1061236808.desc: Configures the delay after the SCL clock edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the delay after the STOP condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

1061236812.name: SCL_STOP_SETUP
1061236812.desc: Configures the delay between the SDA and SCL positive edge for a stop condition

fields.name: TIME
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the time between the positive edge of SCL and the positive edge of SDA, in I2C module clock cycles.

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: When a pulse on the SCL input has smaller width than this register value in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SCL_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SCL.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: When a pulse on the SDA input has smaller width than this register value in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

fields.name: SDA_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the filter enable bit for SDA.

fields.name: COMMAND
fields.desc:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts:

op_code is the command, 0: RSTART. 1: WRITE. 2: READ. 3: STOP. 4: END.

byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.

ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more information.

fields.name: COMMAND_DONE
fields.desc: When command 0 is done in I2C Master mode, this bit changes to high level.

fields.name: SCL_ST_TO
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_FSM state unchanged period.

1061236892.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TIME_OUT
1061236892.desc: SCL main status time out register

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_ST_TO
fields.desc: The threshold value of SCL_MAIN_FSM state unchanged period.

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_EN
fields.desc: When I2C master is IDLE, set this bit to send out SCL pulses. The number of pulses equals to I2C_SCL_RST_SLV_NUM[4:0].

fields.name: SCL_RST_SLV_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the pulses of SCL generated in I2C master mode. Valid when I2C_SCL_RST_SLV_EN is 1.

fields.name: SCL_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SCL line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set I2C_SCL_FORCE_OUT and I2C_SCL_PD_EN to 1 to stretch SCL low.

fields.name: SDA_PD_EN
fields.desc: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SDA line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set I2C_SDA_FORCE_OUT and I2C_SDA_PD_EN to 1 to stretch SDA low.

1061236900.name: SCL_STRETCH_CONF
1061236900.desc: Set SCL stretch of I2C slave

fields.name: STRETCH_PROTECT_NUM
fields.desc: Configure the period of I2C slave stretching SCL line.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_EN
fields.desc: The enable bit for slave SCL stretch function. 1: Enable. 0: Disable. The SCL output line will be stretched low when I2C_SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_EN is 1 and stretch event happens. The stretch cause can be seen in I2C_STRETCH_CAUSE.

fields.name: SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the I2C slave SCL stretch function.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the the version control register.

fields.name: RX_DMA_EQUAL

fields.name: TX_BCK_IN_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for BCK signal into the transmitter based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: TX_WS_IN_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for WS signal into the transmitter based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: RX_BCK_IN_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for BCK signal into the receiver based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: RX_WS_IN_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for WS signal into the receiver based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: RX_SD_IN_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for SD signal into the receiver based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: TX_BCK_OUT_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for BCK signal out of the transmitter based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 0 cycle. 1: delayed by 1 cycle. 2: delayed by 2 cycles. 3: delayed by 3 cycles.

fields.name: TX_WS_OUT_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for WS signal out of the transmitter based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 0 cycle. 1: delayed by 1 cycle. 2: delayed by 2 cycles. 3: delayed by 3 cycles.

fields.name: TX_SD_OUT_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for SD signal out of the transmitter based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 0 cycle. 1: delayed by 1 cycle. 2: delayed by 2 cycles. 3: delayed by 3 cycles.

fields.name: RX_WS_OUT_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for WS signal out of the receiver based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 0 cycle. 1: delayed by 1 cycle. 2: delayed by 2 cycles. 3: delayed by 3 cycles.

fields.name: RX_BCK_OUT_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for BCK signal out of the receiver based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 0 cycle. 1: delayed by 1 cycle. 2: delayed by 2 cycles. 3: delayed by 3 cycles.

fields.name: TX_DSYNC_SW
fields.desc: Set this bit to synchronize signals into the transmitter by two flip-flop synchronizer. 0: the signals will be firstly clocked by rising clock edge , then clocked by falling clock edge. 1: the signals will be firstly clocked by falling clock edge, then clocked by rising clock edge.

fields.name: RX_DSYNC_SW
fields.desc: Set this bit to synchronize signals into the receiver by two flip-flop synchronizer. 0: the signals will be clocked by rising clock edge firstly, then clocked by falling clock edge. 1: the signals will be clocked by falling clock edge firstly, then clocked by rising clock edge.

fields.name: DATA_ENABLE_DELAY
fields.desc: Number of delay cycles for data valid flag based on I2S0_CLK. 0: delayed by 1.5 cycles. 1: delayed by 2.5 cycles. 2: delayed by 3.5 cycles. 3: delayed by 4.5 cycles.

fields.name: TX_BCK_IN_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert BCK signal input to the slave transmitter.

fields.name: RX_DATA_NUM
fields.desc: I2S_RX_TAKE_DATA_INT is triggered when the left and right channel data number in RX FIFO is larger than the value of I2S_RX_DATA_NUM[5:0]. (RX FIFO is almost full threshold.)

fields.name: TX_DATA_NUM
fields.desc: I2S_TX_PUT_DATA_INT is triggered when the left and right channel data number in TX FIFO is smaller than the value of I2S_TX_DATA_NUM[5:0]. (TX FIFO is almost empty threshold.)

fields.name: PRO_APB_PERI_ERROR_INT_MAP
fields.desc: This register is used to map APB_PERI_ERROR_INT interrupt signal to one of the CPU interrupts.

fields.name: PRO_DCACHE_SYNC_INT_MAP
fields.desc: This register is used to map DCACHE_SYNC_INT interrupt signal to one of the CPU interrupts.

fields.name: PRO_ICACHE_SYNC_INT_MAP
fields.desc: This register is used to map ICACHE_SYNC_INT interrupt signal to one of the CPU interrupts.

fields.name: PRO_INTR_STATUS_0
fields.desc: This register stores the status of the first 32 input interrupt sources.

fields.name: PRO_INTR_STATUS_1
fields.desc: This register stores the status of the second 32 input interrupt sources.

fields.name: PRO_INTR_STATUS_2
fields.desc: This register stores the status of the last 31 input interrupt sources.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable or disable the clock of interrupt matrix. 1: enable the clock. 0: disable the clock.

fields.name: PRO_NMI_MASK_HW
fields.desc: This bit is used to disable all NMI interrupt signals to CPU.

fields.name: INTERRUPT_REG_DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: PIN_CLK_OUT1
fields.desc: Configure I2S0 clock output. 0: output I2S0 clock to CLK_OUT1. 15: disabled.

fields.name: PIN_CLK_OUT2
fields.desc: Configure I2S0 clock output. 0: output I2S0 clock to CLK_OUT2. 15: disabled.

fields.name: PIN_CLK_OUT3
fields.desc: Configure I2S0 clock output. 0: output I2S0 clock to CLK_OUT3. 15: disabled.

fields.name: SWITCH_PRT_NUM
fields.desc: IO pin power switch delay, delay unit is one APB clock.

fields.name: PAD_POWER_CTRL
fields.desc: Select power voltage for GPIO33 ~ GPIO37. 1: select VDD_SPI 1.8 V. 0: select VDD3P3_CPU 3.3 V.

fields.name: TIMER_SEL
fields.desc:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer 0.

1: select timer 1.

2: select timer 2.

3: select timer 3.

fields.name: SIG_OUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

fields.name: IDLE_LV
fields.desc: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive.

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: This bit is used to update register LEDC_CH%s_HPOINT and LEDC_CH%s_DUTY for channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1. The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit of LEDC_OVF_CNT_RESET_CH%s.

fields.name: HPOINT
fields.desc: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

fields.name: DUTY
fields.desc: This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint. The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

fields.name: DUTY_SCALE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the changing step scale of duty on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_CYCLE
fields.desc: The duty will change every LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to control the number of times the duty cycle will be changed.

fields.name: DUTY_INC
fields.desc: This register is used to increase or decrease the duty of output signal on channel %s. 1: Increase. 0: Decrease.

fields.name: DUTY_START
fields.desc: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_R
fields.desc: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_RES
fields.desc: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: CLK_DIV
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s. The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

fields.name: PAUSE
fields.desc: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: RST
fields.desc: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

fields.name: TICK_SEL
fields.desc: This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate. 0: LEDC_PWM_CLK. 1: REF_TICK.

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

fields.name: CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

fields.name: TIMER0_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer0 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER1_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer1 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER2_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer2 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.name: TIMER3_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: Triggered when the timer3 has reached its maximum counter value.

fields.desc: Interrupt raw bit for channel 0. Triggered when the gradual change of duty has finished.

fields.name: APB_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: This bit is used to select clock source for the 4 timers . 1: APB_CLK. 2: RTC8M_CLK. 3: XTAL_CLK.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to control clock. 1: Force clock on for register. 0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version control register.

fields.name: FILTER_THRES
fields.desc:
This sets the maximum threshold, in APB_CLK cycles, for the filter.
Any pulses with width less than this will be ignored when the filter is enabled.

fields.name: FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for unit %s's input filter.

fields.name: CH0_NEG_MODE

fields.name: CH1_POS_MODE

fields.name: CH1_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:

fields.name: DMA_TX_I_ILG_ST
fields.desc: Record the illegitimate information of TX Copy DMA. [22:6]: store the bits [18:2] of address. [5]: if bits [31:19] of address are 0x7ff, then the bit value is 1, otherwise it is 0. [4]: 1 means write operation, 0 means read operation. [3:0]: TX Copy DMA bus byte enables.

fields.name: DATA
fields.desc: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL%s by apb fifo access.

fields.name: DIV_CNT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: IDLE_THRES
fields.desc: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EFF_EN
fields.desc: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV
fields.desc:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_WR_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

fields.name: MEM_RD_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER
fields.desc:
This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.

1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 

1'h0: Transmitter is using the ram.

fields.name: TX_CONTI_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

fields.name: CHK_RX_CARRIER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable memory loop read mode when carrier modulation is enabled for channel %s.

fields.name: REF_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc:
This bit is used to select the base clock for CHANNEL%s.

1'h1: clk_apb    1'h0:clk_ref

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_LV
fields.desc: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

fields.name: TX_STOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

fields.name: MEM_WADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when receiver of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.name: MEM_RADDR_EX
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when transmitter of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the ownership of memory block is wrong.

fields.name: MEM_FULL
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the receiver receives more data than the memory size.

fields.name: MEM_EMPTY
fields.desc: This status bit will be set when the data to be set is more than memory size and the wraparound mode is disabled.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WR_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when writes via APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RD_ERR
fields.desc: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reads via APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when writes RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register records the memory address offset when reads RAM over APB bus.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when transmission done.

fields.name: CH%s_RX_END
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when reception done.

fields.name: CH%s_ERR
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when error occurs.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_THR_EVENT
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when transmitter sent more data than configured value.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_LOOP
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for CHANNEL%s. Triggered when the loop count reaches the configured threshold value.

fields.name: CH%s_TX_LOOP
fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit for CH%s_TX_LOOP_INT.

fields.name: CARRIER_HIGH
fields.desc: This register is used to configure carrier wave 's high level clock period for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: TX_LIM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum entries that CHANNEL%s can send out.

fields.name: TX_LOOP_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum loop count when tx_conti_mode is valid.

fields.name: TX_LOOP_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This register is the enabled bit for loop count.

fields.name: LOOP_COUNT_RESET
fields.desc: This register is used to reset the loop count when tx_conti_mode is valid.

fields.name: APB_FIFO_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: access memory directly.   1'h0: access memory by FIFO.

fields.name: MEM_TX_WRAP_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the clock for RMT memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to power down RMT memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: 1: Disable RMT memory light sleep power down function. 0: Power down RMT memory when RMT is in light sleep mode.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: RMT register clock gate enable signal. 1: Power up the drive clock of registers. 0: Power down the drive clock of registers

fields.name: CH0

fields.name: CH1

fields.name: CH2

fields.name: CH3

fields.name: EN

fields.name: CARRIER_HIGH_THRES
fields.desc: The high level period in a carrier modulation mode is (REG_RMT_REG_CARRIER_HIGH_THRES_CH%s + 1) for channel %s.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: M_PRIME
fields.desc: Stores M'.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: Stores the mode of modular exponentiation.

fields.name: CLEAN
fields.desc: The content of this bit is 1 when memories complete initialization.

fields.name: MODEXP_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to start the modular exponentiation.

fields.name: MODMULT_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to start the modular multiplication.

fields.name: MULT_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to start the multiplication.

fields.name: IDLE
fields.desc: The content of this bit is 1 when the RSA accelerator is idle.

fields.name: CLEAR_INTERRUPT
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to clear the RSA interrupts.

fields.name: CONSTANT_TIME
fields.desc: Set this bit to 0 to enable the acceleration option of constant_time for modular exponentiation. Set to 1 to disable the acceleration (by default).

fields.name: SEARCH_ENABLE
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable the acceleration option of search for modular exponentiation. Set to 0 to disable the acceleration (by default).

fields.name: SEARCH_POS
fields.desc: Is used to configure the starting address when the acceleration option of search is used.

fields.name: INTERRUPT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable the RSA interrupt. This option is enabled by default.

fields.name: GPIO_OUT_DATA_W1TS
fields.desc: GPIO0 ~ 21 output set register. If the value 1 is written to a bit here, the corresponding bit in RTCIO_RTC_GPIO_OUT_REG will be set to 1. Recommended operation: use this register to set RTCIO_RTC_GPIO_OUT_REG.

1061192712.name: RTC_GPIO_OUT_W1TC

fields.desc: GPIO0 ~ 21 output clear register. If the value 1 is written to a bit here, the corresponding bit in RTCIO_RTC_GPIO_OUT_REG will be cleared. Recommended operation: use this register to clear RTCIO_RTC_GPIO_OUT_REG.

fields.name: REG_RTCIO_REG_GPIO_ENABLE
fields.desc: GPIO0 ~ 21 output enable. Bit10 corresponds to GPIO0, bit11 corresponds to GPIO1, etc. If the bit is set to 1, it means this GPIO pad is output.

1610854408.name: T_LENGTH
1610854408.desc: String length register for calculating initial Hash Value (only effective for SHA-512/t)

fields.name: T_LENGTH

1610854432.name: DMA_CONTINUE

fields.desc: Write 1 to continue DMA-SHA calculation.

fields.name: INTERRUPT_ENA

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Version control register.

fields.name: H

fields.name: M
fields.desc: Stores the %sth 32-bit piece of the message.

fields.name: CONF_BITLEN
fields.desc: Define the spi_clk cycles of  SPI_CONF state. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable. Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_VALUE
fields.desc: [31:8]:address to slave, [7:0]:Reserved. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: EXT_HOLD_EN
fields.desc: Set the bit to hold spi. The bit is combined with SPI_USR_PREP_HOLD,SPI_USR_CMD_HOLD,SPI_USR_ADDR_HOLD,SPI_USR_DUMMY_HOLD,SPI_USR_DIN_HOLD,SPI_USR_DOUT_HOLD and SPI_USR_HOLD_POL. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase the signal level of spi is output by the spi controller. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2-bit mode during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4-bit mode during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8-bit mode during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2-bit mode during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4-bit mode during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8-bit mode during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase is in 2-bit mode. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase is in 4-bit mode. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_OCT
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase is in 8-bit mode. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RD_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WR_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_MODE_13
fields.desc: {CPOL, CPHA},1: support spi clk mode 1 and 3, first edge output data B[0]/B[7].  0: support spi clk mode 0 and 2, first edge output data B[1]/B[6].

fields.name: RSCK_DATA_OUT
fields.desc: It saves half a cycle when tsck is the same as rsck. 1: output data at rsck posedge   0: output data at tsck posedge

fields.name: W16_17_WR_ENA
fields.desc: 1:SPI_BUF16~SPI_BUF17 can be written   0:SPI_BUF16~SPI_BUF17 can not  be written. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: SPI cs signal is delayed by spi clock cycles. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with SPI_CS_SETUP bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with SPI_CS_HOLD bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_DELAY_MODE
fields.desc: spi_cs signal is delayed by spi_clk . 0: zero 1: if SPI_CK_OUT_EDGE or SPI_CK_IDLE_EDGE is set 1 delayed by half cycle  else delayed by one cycle 2: if SPI_CK_OUT_EDGE or  SPI_CK_IDLE_EDGE is set 1 delayed by one cycle, else delayed by half cycle 3: delayed one cycle. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: spi_cs signal is delayed by system clock cycles. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to SPI_CLKCNT_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((SPI_CLKCNT_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(SPI_CLKDIV_PRE+1)/(SPI_CLKCNT_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKDIV_PRE
fields.desc: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DOUTDIN
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QPI_MODE
fields.desc: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: OPI_MODE
fields.desc: Just for master mode. 1: spi controller is in OPI mode (all in 8-bit mode). 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with SPI_DOUT_MODE register to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RD_BYTE_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: big-endian 0: little_endian. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WR_BYTE_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: big-endian 0: litte_endian. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase is in 2-bit mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase is in 4-bit mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_OCT
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase is in 8-bit mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_CONF_NXT
fields.desc: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_HOLD_POL
fields.desc: It is combined with hold bits to set the polarity of spi hold line 1: spi will be held when spi hold line is high 0: spi will be held when spi hold line is low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DOUT_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at data out state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DIN_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at data in state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at dummy state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at address state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_CMD_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at command state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_PREP_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at prepare state the bit are combined with SPI_USR_HOLD_POL bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer SPI_BUF8~SPI_BUF17. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer SPI_BUF8~SPI_BUF17. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_DBITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of write-data. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO_DBITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of  read-data. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS0_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS0 pin enable, 1: disable CS0, 0: SPI_CS0 signal is from/to CS0 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS1_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS1 pin enable, 1: disable CS1, 0: SPI_CS1 signal is from/to CS1 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS2_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS2 pin enable, 1: disable CS2, 0: SPI_CS2 signal is from/to CS2 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS3_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS3 pin enable, 1: disable CS3, 0: SPI_CS3 signal is from/to CS3 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS4_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS4 pin enable, 1: disable CS4, 0: SPI_CS4 signal is from/to CS4 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS5_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS5 pin enable, 1: disable CS5, 0: SPI_CS5 signal is from/to CS5 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_DIS
fields.desc: 1: spi clk out disable,  0: spi clk out enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MASTER_CS_POL
fields.desc: In the master mode the bits are the polarity of spi cs line, the value is equivalent to spi_cs ^ SPI_MASTER_CS_POL. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI master DTR mode is applied to SPI clk, data and spi_dqs.  0: SPI master DTR mode is  only applied to spi_dqs. This bit should be used with bit 17/18/19.

fields.name: DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: ADDR_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CMD_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CD_DATA_SET
fields.desc: 1: spi_cd = !SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE when SPI_ST[3:0] is in SPI_DOUT or SPI_DIN state.  0: spi_cd = SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CD_DUMMY_SET
fields.desc: 1: spi_cd = !SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE when SPI_ST[3:0] is in SPI_DUMMY state.  0: spi_cd = SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CD_ADDR_SET
fields.desc: 1: spi_cd = !SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE when SPI_ST[3:0] is in SPI_SEND_ADDR state.  0: spi_cd = SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SLAVE_CS_POL
fields.desc: spi slave input cs polarity select. 1: inv  0: not change. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DQS_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: The default value of spi_dqs. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CD_CMD_SET
fields.desc: 1: spi_cd = !SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE when SPI_ST[3:0] is in SPI_SEND_CMD state.  0: spi_cd = SPI_CD_IDLE_EDGE. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CD_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: The default value of spi_cd. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: spi clk line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QUAD_DIN_PIN_SWAP
fields.desc: 1:  spi quad input swap enable  0:  spi quad input swap disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TRANS_DONE
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for the completion of any operation in both the master mode and the slave mode.  Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: INT_RD_BUF_DONE_EN
fields.desc: SPI_SLV_RD_BUF_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: INT_WR_BUF_DONE_EN
fields.desc: SPI_SLV_WR_BUF_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: INT_RD_DMA_DONE_EN
fields.desc: SPI_SLV_RD_DMA_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: INT_WR_DMA_DONE_EN
fields.desc: SPI_SLV_WR_DMA_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: INT_TRANS_DONE_EN
fields.desc: SPI_TRANS_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: INT_DMA_SEG_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: SPI_DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE Interrupt enable. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable seg magic value error interrupt. 0: Others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TRANS_CNT
fields.desc: The operations counter in both the master mode and the slave mode.

fields.name: TRANS_DONE_AUTO_CLR_EN
fields.desc: SPI_TRANS_DONE auto clear enable, clear it 3 apb cycles after the pos edge of SPI_TRANS_DONE.  0:disable. 1: enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: Set SPI work mode. 1: slave mode 0: master mode.

fields.name: SOFT_RESET
fields.desc: Software reset enable, reset the spi clock line cs line and data lines. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SLV_ADDR_ERR_CLR
fields.desc: 1: Clear SPI_SLV_ADDR_ERR. 0: not valid. Can be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: SLV_CMD_ERR_CLR
fields.desc: 1: Clear SPI_SLV_CMD_ERR. 0: not valid.  Can be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: SLV_NO_QPI_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi slave QPI mode is not supported. 0: spi slave QPI mode is supported.

fields.name: SLV_ADDR_ERR
fields.desc: 1: The address value of the last SPI transfer is not supported by SPI slave. 0: The address value is supported or no address value is received.

fields.name: SLV_CMD_ERR
fields.desc: 1: The command value of the last SPI transfer is not supported by SPI slave. 0: The command value is supported or no command value is received.

fields.name: SLV_WR_DMA_DONE
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for the completion of dma write operation in the slave mode.  Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: SLV_LAST_COMMAND
fields.desc: In the slave mode it is the value of command.

fields.name: SLV_LAST_ADDR
fields.desc: In the slave mode it is the value of address.

1061171256.name: SLV_WRBUF_DLEN
1061171256.desc: SPI slave Wr_BUF interrupt and CONF control register

fields.name: SLV_WR_BUF_DONE
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for the completion of write-buffer operation in the slave mode.  Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: CONF_BASE_BITLEN
fields.desc: The basic spi_clk cycles of CONF state. The real cycle length of CONF state, if SPI_USR_CONF is enabled, is SPI_CONF_BASE_BITLEN[6:0] + SPI_CONF_BITLEN[23:0].

1061171260.name: SLV_RDBUF_DLEN
1061171260.desc: SPI magic error and slave control register

fields.name: SLV_DMA_RD_BYTELEN
fields.desc: In the slave mode it is the length in bytes for read operations. The register value shall be byte_num.

fields.name: SLV_RD_BUF_DONE
fields.desc: The interrupt raw bit for the completion of read-buffer operation in the slave mode.  Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: SEG_MAGIC_ERR
fields.desc: 1: The recent magic value in CONF buffer is not right in master DMA seg-trans mode. 0: others.

fields.name: SLV_DATA_BYTELEN
fields.desc: The full-duplex or half-duplex data byte length of the last SPI transfer in slave mode. In half-duplex mode, this value is controlled by bits [23:20].

fields.name: SLV_RDDMA_BYTELEN_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI_SLV_DATA_BYTELEN stores data byte length of master-read-slave data length in DMA controlled mode(Rd_DMA). 0: others

fields.name: INT_HOLD_ENA
fields.desc: This register is for two SPI masters to share the same cs clock and data signals. The bits of one SPI are set, if the other SPI is busy, the SPI will be hold. 1(3): hold at  idle  phase 2: hold at  prepare  phase. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: VAL
fields.desc: spi hold output value, which should be used with SPI_HOLD_OUT_EN. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: OUT_EN

fields.name: OUT_TIME

fields.desc: Cycles that release calibration timeout reset

fields.name: TIMERS_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate signal. 1: Registers can be read and written to by software. 0: Registers can not be read or written to by software.

fields.name: RESET_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the operating mode of the TWAI Controller. 1: Reset mode; 0: Operating mode.

fields.name: LISTEN_ONLY_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Listen only mode. In this mode the nodes will only receive messages from the bus, without generating the acknowledge signal nor updating the RX error counter.

fields.name: SELF_TEST_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Self test mode. In this mode the TX nodes can perform a successful transmission without receiving the acknowledge signal. This mode is often used to test a single node with the self reception request command.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the filter mode. 0: Dual filter mode; 1: Single filter mode.

fields.name: TX_REQ
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to allow the driving nodes start transmission.

fields.name: ABORT_TX
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to cancel a pending transmission request.

fields.name: RELEASE_BUF
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to release the RX buffer.

fields.name: CLR_OVERRUN
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to clear the data overrun status bit.

fields.name: SELF_RX_REQ
fields.desc: Self reception request command. Set the bit to 1 to allow a message be transmitted and received simultaneously.

fields.name: RX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The data in the RX buffer is not empty, with at least one received data packet.

fields.name: OVERRUN_ST
fields.desc: 1: The RX FIFO is full and data overrun has occurred.

fields.name: TX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TX buffer is empty, the CPU may write a message into it.

fields.name: TX_COMPLETE
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI controller has successfully received a packet from the bus.

fields.name: RX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is receiving a message from the bus.

fields.name: TX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is transmitting a message to the bus.

fields.name: ERR_ST
fields.desc: 1: At least one of the RX/TX error counter has reached or exceeded the value set in register TWAI_ERR_WARNING_LIMIT_REG.

fields.name: BUS_OFF_ST
fields.desc: 1: In bus-off status, the TWAI Controller is no longer involved in bus activities.

fields.name: MISS_ST
fields.desc: This bit reflects whether the data packet in the RX FIFO is complete. 1: The current packet is missing; 0: The current packet is complete

fields.name: RX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Receive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates there are messages to be handled in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: TX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Transmit interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the message transmitting mis- sion is finished and a new transmission is able to execute.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error warning interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the error status signal and the bus-off status signal of Status register have changed (e.g., switched from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0).

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Data overrun interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates a data overrun interrupt is generated in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error passive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the TWAI Controller is switched between error active status and error passive status due to the change of error counters.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ST
fields.desc: Arbitration lost interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an arbitration lost interrupt is generated.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an error is detected on the bus.

fields.name: RX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable receive interrupt.

fields.name: TX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable transmit interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error warning interrupt.

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable data overrun interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error passive interrupt.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable arbitration lost interrupt.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error interrupt.

fields.name: BAUD_PRESC
fields.desc: Baud Rate Prescaler, determines the frequency dividing ratio.

fields.name: SYNC_JUMP_WIDTH
fields.desc: Synchronization Jump Width (SJW), 1 \verb+~+ 14 Tq wide.

fields.name: TIME_SEG1
fields.desc: The width of PBS1.

fields.name: TIME_SEG2
fields.desc: The width of PBS2.

fields.name: TIME_SAMP
fields.desc: The number of sample points. 0: the bus is sampled once; 1: the bus is sampled three times

fields.name: ARB_LOST_CAP
fields.desc: This register contains information about the bit position of lost arbitration.

fields.name: ECC_SEGMENT
fields.desc: This register contains information about the location of errors, see Table 181 for details.

fields.name: ECC_DIRECTION
fields.desc: This register contains information about transmission direction of the node when error occurs. 1: Error occurs when receiving a message; 0: Error occurs when transmitting a message

fields.name: ECC_TYPE
fields.desc: This register contains information about error types: 00: bit error; 01: form error; 10: stuff error; 11: other type of error

fields.name: ERR_WARNING_LIMIT
fields.desc: Error warning threshold. In the case when any of a error counter value exceeds the threshold, or all the error counter values are below the threshold, an error warning interrupt will be triggered (given the enable signal is valid).

fields.name: RX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The RX error counter register, reflects value changes under reception status.

fields.name: TX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The TX error counter register, reflects value changes under transmission status.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_0
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 0th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_1
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 1st byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_2
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 2nd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_3
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 3rd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_4
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 4th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_5
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 5th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_6
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 6th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_7
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 7th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_8
fields.desc: Stored the 8th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_9
fields.desc: Stored the 9th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_10

fields.name: TX_BYTE_12

fields.name: RXFIFO_RD_BYTE

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver receives more data than what UART_RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD specifies.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in TX FIFO is less than what UART_TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD specifies.

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a parity error in the data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a data frame error.

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver receives more data than the capacity of RX FIFO.

fields.name: DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver takes more time than UART_RX_TOUT_THRHD to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver receives an XON character and UART_SW_FLOW_CON_EN is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver receives an XOFF character and UART_SW_FLOW_CON_EN is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters, after all data in TX FIFO are sent.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the transmitter has sent out all data in FIFO.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a parity error from the echo of the transmitter in RS485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects a data frame error from the echo of the transmitter in RS485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_CLASH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when a collision is detected between the transmitter and the receiver in RS485 mode.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the receiver detects the configured UART_AT_CMD CHAR.

fields.name: WAKEUP_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input RXD edge changes more times than what UART_ACTIVE_THRESHOLD specifies in Light-sleep mode.
