This register is used in autobaud detection.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the number of valid data bytes in RX FIFO.

fields.name: DSRN
fields.desc: This register represents the level of the internal UART DSR signal.

fields.name: CTSN
fields.desc: This register represents the level of the internal UART CTS signal.

fields.name: RXD
fields.desc: This register represents the level of the internal UART RXD signal.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the number of data bytes in TX FIFO.

fields.name: DTRN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal UART DTR signal.

fields.name: RTSN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal UART RTS signal.

fields.name: TXD
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal UART TXD signal.

fields.name: PARITY
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the parity check mode.
0: even. 1: odd.

fields.name: PARITY_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART parity check.

fields.name: BIT_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to set the length of data.
0: 5 bits. 1: 6 bits. 2: 7 bits. 3: 8 bits.

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to set the length of  stop bit.
1: 1 bit. 2: 1.5 bits. 3: 2 bits.

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software RTS signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: SW_DTR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software DTR signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: TXD_BRK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to send NULL characters when the process of sending data is done.

fields.name: IRDA_DPLX
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA loopback mode.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_EN
fields.desc: This is the start enable bit for IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_WCTL
fields.desc: 1: The IrDA transmitter's 11th bit is the same as 10th bit. 0: Set IrDA transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_RX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA receiver.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable flow control function for the transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA protocol.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the UART RX FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the UART TX FIFO.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART RXD signal.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART CTS signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART DSR signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART TXD signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART RTS signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of UART DTR signal.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1: Force clock on for registers. 0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1: The receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 0: The receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: TICK_REF_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc:
This register is used to select the clock. 
1: APB_CLK. 
0: REF_TICK.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc:
The signal to enable UART RAM clock gating.
1: UART RAM powers on, the data of which can be read and written.
0: UART RAM powers down.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: An UART_RXFIFO_FULL_INT interrupt is generated when the receiver receives more data than this register’s value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: An UART_TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT interrupt is generated when the number of data bytes in TX FIFO is less than this register's value.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc:
This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.
1: Choose software flow control with configuring sw_rts signal. 0: Disable software flow control.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for UART receiver's timeout function.

1061158952.name: LOWPULSE
1061158952.desc: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate detection.

1061158956.name: HIGHPULSE
1061158956.desc: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores  the value of the maximum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate detection.

fields.name: RXD_EDGE_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the count of RXD edge change.  It is used in baud rate detection. As baud rate registers UART_REG_LOWPULSE_MIN_CNT, UART_REG_HIGHPULSE_MIN_CNT, UART_REG_POSEDGE_MIN_CNT, and UART_REG_NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT always record the minimal value, UART_REG_RXD_EDGE_CNT indicates the statistic number of RXD edge to find out the minimal value for these baud rate registers.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. When UART receives flow control characters XON or XOFF, which can be configured by UART_XON_CHAR or UART_XOFF_CHAR respectively, UART_SW_XON_INT or UART_SW_XOFF_INT interrupts can be triggered if enabled.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control characters from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to force the transmitter to send data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send an XON character. This bit is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send an XOFF character. This bit is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The UART is activated from Light-sleep mode when the input RXD edge changes more times than this register's value.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the number of data bytes in RX FIFO is more than this register's value with UART_SW_FLOW_CON_EN set to 1, the transmitter sends an XOFF character.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the XOFF flow control character.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the number of data bytes in RX FIFO is less than this register's value with UART_SW_FLOW_CON_EN set to 1, the transmitter sends an XON character.

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the XON flow control character.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: A frame end signal is generated when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register's value, in the unit of bit time (the time it takes to transfer one bit).

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers, in the unit of bit time (the time it takes to transfer one bit).

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when UART_TXD_BRK is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to choose RS485 mode.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: RS485TX_RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in RS485 mode.

fields.name: RS485RXBY_TX_EN
fields.desc:
1: enable RS485 transmitter to send data when RS485 receiver line is busy. 
0: RS485 transmitter should not send data when its receiver is busy.

fields.name: RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

fields.name: RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first AT_CMD is received by the receiver. 
It will not take the next data received as AT_CMD character when the duration is less than this register's value.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the duration time between the last AT_CMD and the next data.
It will not take the previous data as AT_CMD character when the duration is less than this register's value.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the duration time between the AT_CMD characters.
It will not take the data as continuous AT_CMD characters when the duration time is less than this register's value.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of AT_CMD character.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of continuous AT_CMD characters received by the receiver.

fields.name: RX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of RAM allocated for RX FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: TX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of RAM allocated for TX FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data bytes that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the threshold time that the receiver takes to receive one byte, in the unit of bit time (the time it takes to transfer one bit).
The UART_RXFIFO_TOUT_INT interrupt will be triggered when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with UART RX_TOUT_EN set to 1.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART RAM.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART RAM.

1061159008.name: MEM_TX_STATUS
1061159008.desc: TX FIFO write and read offset address

fields.name: APB_TX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in TX FIFO when software writes TX FIFO via APB.

fields.name: TX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in TX FIFO when TX FSM reads data via Tx_FIFO_Ctrl.

1061159012.name: MEM_RX_STATUS
1061159012.desc: RX FIFO write and read offset address

fields.name: APB_RX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in RX_FIFO when software reads data from RX FIFO via APB.

fields.name: RX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in RX FIFO when Rx_FIFO_Ctrl writes RX FIFO.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of the receiver.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of the transmitter.

fields.name: POSEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in baud rate detection.

fields.name: NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in baud rate detection.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version control register.

fields.name: ID
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the UART_ID.

fields.name: IN_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset in DMA FSM.

fields.name: OUT_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset out DMA FSM.

fields.name: AHBM_FIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset AHB interface cmdFIFO of DMA.

fields.name: AHBM_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset AHB interface of DMA.

fields.name: IN_LOOP_TEST
fields.desc: Reserved.

fields.name: OUT_LOOP_TEST
fields.desc: Reserved.

fields.name: OUT_AUTO_WRBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable automatic outlink writeback when all the data in TX FIFO has been transmitted.

fields.name: OUT_NO_RESTART_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_MODE
fields.desc:
This register is used to specify the generation mode of UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT interrupt. 
1: When DMA has popped all data from FIFO.
0: When AHB has pushed all data to FIFO.

fields.name: UART0_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up UHCI and UART0.

fields.name: UART1_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up UHCI and UART1.

fields.name: OUTDSCR_BURST_EN
fields.desc:
This register is used to specify DMA transmit descriptor transfer mode.
1: burst mode.
0: byte mode.

fields.name: INDSCR_BURST_EN
fields.desc:
This register is used to specify DMA receive descriptor transfer mode.
1: burst mode.
0: byte mode.

fields.name: MEM_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: 1: UHCI transmitted data would be write back into DMA INFIFO.

fields.name: SEPER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to separate the data frame using a special character.

fields.name: HEAD_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a formatting header.

fields.name: CRC_REC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UHCI to receive the 16 bit CRC.

fields.name: UART_IDLE_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI will end the payload receiving process when UART has been in idle state.

fields.name: LEN_EOF_EN
fields.desc:
If this bit is set to 1, UHCI decoder stops receiving payload data when the number of received data bytes has reached the specified value. 
The value is payload length indicated by UCHI packet header when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 1 or the value is a configuration value when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0. 
If this bit is set to 0, UHCI decoder stops receiving payload data  upon receiving 0xC0.

fields.name: ENCODE_CRC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable data integrity checking by appending a 16 bit CCITT-CRC to the end of the payload.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1: Force clock on for registers. 0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: UART_RX_BRK_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI stops receiving payload data when a NULL frame is received by UART.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when a separator has been sent.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_TX_START_INT  interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when DMA detects a separator.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when DMA takes more time to receive data than the configure value.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT  interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when DMA takes more time to read data from RAM than the configured value.

fields.name: IN_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_IN_DONE_INT  interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when an receive descriptor is completed.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_IN_SUC_EOF_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when a data packet has been received successfully.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_IN_ERR_EOF_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when there are some errors in EOF in the receive descriptor.

fields.name: OUT_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_OUT_DONE_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when an transmit descriptor is completed.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when the current descriptor's EOF bit is 1.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when there are some errors in the receive descriptor.

fields.name: OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when there are some errors in the transmit descriptor.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when there are not enough inlinks for DMA.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when there are some errors in EOF in the transmit descriptor.

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when all data in the last buffer address has been sent out.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when DMA has sent out a short packet using single_send mode.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when DMA has sent out a short packet using always_send mode.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit for UHCI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT interrupt. The interrupt is triggered when the number of data bytes in DMA RX FIFO has reached the configured threshold value.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt when UHCI_RX_START_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt when UHCI_TX_START_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt when UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt when UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: IN_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_IN_DONE_INT interrupt when UHCI_IN_DONE_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_IN_SUC_EOF_INT interrupt when UHCI_IN_SUC_EOF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_IN_ERR_EOF_INT interrupt when UHCI_IN_ERR_EOF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: OUT_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_OUT_DONE_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUT_DONE_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt when UHCI_IN_DSCR_ERR_INT is set to 1.

fields.name: OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT interrupt when UHCI_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for  UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for  UHCI_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for  UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT interrupt when UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT interrupt when UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT INTERRUPT when UHCI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT_ENA is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DONE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_IN_DONE_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_IN_SUC_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_IN_ERR_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_DONE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUT_DONE_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DONE_INT_CLR

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_INT_CLR

fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_IN_ERR_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_DONE_INT_CLR

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_CLR

fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_FULL
fields.desc: 1: DMA TX FIFO is full.

fields.name: OUT_EMPTY
fields.desc: 1: DMA TX FIFO is empty.

1061240856.name: DMA_OUT_PUSH
1061240856.desc: Push control register of TX FIFO

fields.name: OUTFIFO_WDATA
fields.desc: This is the data that need to be pushed into TX FIFO.

fields.name: OUTFIFO_PUSH
fields.desc: Set this bit to push data into TX FIFO.

fields.name: IN_FULL
fields.desc: Data-input FIFO full signal.

fields.name: IN_EMPTY
fields.desc: Data-input FIFO empty signal.

fields.name: RX_ERR_CAUSE

1061240864.name: DMA_IN_POP
1061240864.desc: Pop control register of RX FIFO

fields.name: INFIFO_RDATA
fields.desc: This register stores the data popping from RX FIFO.

fields.name: INFIFO_POP
fields.desc: Set this bit to pop data from  RX FIFO.

fields.name: OUTLINK_ADDR
fields.desc: This register is used to specify the least significant 20 bits of the first transmit descriptor's address.

fields.name: OUTLINK_STOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop dealing with the transmit descriptor.

fields.name: OUTLINK_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start a new transmit descriptor.

fields.name: OUTLINK_RESTART

fields.name: OUTLINK_PARK
fields.desc:
1: the transmit descriptor's FSM is in idle state.

fields.name: INLINK_ADDR
fields.desc: This register is used to specify the least significant 20 bits of the first receive descriptor's address.

fields.name: INLINK_AUTO_RET
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to return to current receive descriptor's address, when there are some errors in current packet.

fields.name: INLINK_STOP
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop dealing with the receive descriptors.

fields.name: INLINK_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start dealing with the receive descriptors.

fields.name: INLINK_RESTART
fields.desc: Set this bit to restart new receive descriptors.

fields.name: INLINK_PARK
fields.desc:
1: the receive descriptor's FSM is in idle state.
0: the receive descriptor's FSM is working.

fields.name: CHECK_SUM_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check header checksum when UHCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: CHECK_SEQ_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check sequence number when UHCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: CRC_DISABLE
fields.desc: Set this bit to support CRC calculation. Data Integrity check present bit in UHCI packet frame should be 1.

fields.name: SAVE_HEAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to save the packet header when UHCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: TX_CHECK_SUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a checksum.

fields.name: TX_ACK_NUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with an acknowledgement when a reliable packet is to be transmit.

fields.name: CHECK_OWNER
fields.desc: 1: Check the link list descriptor when link list owner is DMA controller; 0: Always check link list descriptor.

fields.name: WAIT_SW_START
fields.desc: The UHCI encoder will jump to ST_SW_WAIT status if this register is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_START
fields.desc: If current UHCI_ENCODE_STATE is ST_SW_WAIT, the UHCI will start to send data packet out when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_THRS

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA

fields.name: STATE
